  "prompt": "How many pictures does a 2GB SD card hold?",
  "response": "The number of pictures a 2GB SD card can hold depends on several factors, including the image resolution and file format of the pictures. For example:\n\n- **JPEG images**: A standard JPEG image can range from about 1MB to 5MB each, depending on the camera settings. If we take an average of about 2MB per JPEG image, a 2GB SD card could hold approximately 1,000 pictures (2GB = 2048MB; 2048MB \u00f7 2MB \u2248 1024 images).\n\n- **Raw images**: If you're taking photos in RAW format, these files are significantly larger, often ranging from 10MB to 30MB or more, depending on the camera. In this case, a 2GB card would hold significantly fewer images\u2014potentially around 100 to 200 RAW images, if we assume an average size of 10MB.\n\nThus, the number of pictures a 2GB SD card can hold can vary widely based on the file size of each photo.",
